# ~/automations — the `automations` branch of superclaude. CODE ONLY.
# Everything sensitive/runtime lives on toto and NEVER travels (WT-2/WT-3).

# SSOT identikits + document locker + living docs + career archive (PII, toto-only)
ssot/
documents/
docs/
career-archive/

# ...but the engine's OWN docs are code, not PII: the bare `docs/` above matches at
# every depth, so it swallows engine-build/docs/ too. The vendor-ToS record is the
# evidence the essay automation stands on (which platform forbids AI-written
# answers, which requires a disclosure): it ships with the engine or the policy it
# encodes is unauditable.
#
# Three lines, not two, and the middle one is load-bearing: un-ignoring the
# DIRECTORY alone would un-ignore everything inside it, so the next file dropped in
# engine-build/docs/ (a scratch note, a CV excerpt) would be committable by
# default. Re-excluding the contents keeps the guard FAIL-CLOSED: each engine doc
# is named explicitly or it stays ignored.
!engine-build/docs/
engine-build/docs/*
!engine-build/docs/vendor-tos.md

# Secrets + runtime data
.env
*.env
!*.env.example
ntfy/credentials
ntfy/inbox.jsonl
discovery/pull.log
*.age
*.db
*.db-wal
*.db-shm

# Local envs + caches + stray project dirs
.venv/
**/__pycache__/
*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
**/.claude/
*.log
